  "prompt": "Will there be a sufficient space for rough work in offline mode of JEE?",
  "response": "Yes, in the offline mode of the Joint Entrance Examination (JEE), there is typically sufficient space provided for rough work. The question paper usually contains blank pages or designated areas where candidates can perform calculations and jot down notes. Additionally, students are allowed to bring their own stationery, such as pens, pencils, and erasers, to facilitate their rough work during the exam. However, it is important to make sure you do not write anything on the answer sheet other than your answers, as this could lead to disqualification or penalization. Always follow the instructions provided by the examination authorities regarding rough work.",
